<meta name=3D"DC.Title" content=3D"Fibonacci Number">
=09
<meta name=3D"DC.Creator" content=3D"Weisstein, Eric W.">
=09
<meta name=3D"DC.Description" content=3D"The Fibonacci numbers are the sequ=
ence of numbers {F_n}_(n=3D1)^infty defined by the linear recurrence equati=
on  F_n=3DF_(n-1)+F_(n-2)  (1)   with F_1=3DF_2=3D1. As a result of the def=
inition (1), it is conventional to define F_0=3D0. The Fibonacci numbers fo=
r n=3D1, 2, ... are 1, 1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 13, 21, ... (OEIS A000045). Fibonacci=
 numbers can be viewed as a particular case of the Fibonacci polynomials F_=
n(x) with F_n=3DF_n(1). Fibonacci numbers are implemented in the Wolfram La=
nguage as Fibonacci[n]....">
=09
<meta name=3D"description" content=3D"The Fibonacci numbers are the sequenc=
e of numbers {F_n}_(n=3D1)^infty defined by the linear recurrence equation =
 F_n=3DF_(n-1)+F_(n-2)  (1)   with F_1=3DF_2=3D1. As a result of the defini=
tion (1), it is conventional to define F_0=3D0. The Fibonacci numbers for n=
=3D1, 2, ... are 1, 1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 13, 21, ... (OEIS A000045). Fibonacci nu=
mbers can be viewed as a particular case of the Fibonacci polynomials F_n(x=
) with F_n=3DF_n(1). Fibonacci numbers are implemented in the Wolfram Langu=
age as Fibonacci[n]....">
